The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Tuesday, November 2, 2004

 Road to avoid

 S.P Mukherjee Road. One flank barricaded for civic work.

 Tax talk

 A discussion on the proposal to replace state sales tax by an all-India value-added tax system, organised by Committee on Public Affairs, at Great Eastern Hotel, 5.30 pm. Former mayor of Calcutta Kamal Kumar Basu will preside. Speakers include Nirmal Chandra, Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharya and Ashok Mitra. 

 Soiree

 A classical guitar recital by Genevi?ve Chanut, organised by Alliance Francaise de Calcutta, at Calcutta School of Music, 7 pm.

 In camera

 Native Women of South India ? Manners and Customs, an exhibition of photographs by Pushpamala N. and Clare Arni, will be opened at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 6 pm.

 Sixth Photo Festival 2004 of colour monochrome photographs and slide shows at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.

 Launch 

 Moving On by Shashi Deshpande will be launched at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm. Professor P. Lal will attend.

 Art beat

 Exhibitions by Debangshu Das and Naba Kishore to be opened at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture, 4.30 pm and 5 pm respectively.




